                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="16517621" author="lindong" created="Tue, 19 Jun 2018 23:22:43 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Moving from 1.1.1 to 1.1.2 as&#160;there is no open PR&#160;for 1.1.1.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16523885" author="enether" created="Tue, 26 Jun 2018 15:46:30 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Changing them to the first approach (count both inbound/outbound connections) might mess up some Kafka users&apos; metrics - imagine watching your connections blow up in numbers over a patch update.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I believe we should separate out the sensors and offer both metrics - inbound, outbound. This will enable the UIs to provide the three kinds of metrics (in, out, total).&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=apovzner&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;apovzner&quot;&gt;apovzner&lt;/a&gt;, what do you think?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16523905" author="ijuma" created="Tue, 26 Jun 2018 16:00:54 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=enether&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;enether&quot;&gt;enether&lt;/a&gt;, these metrics exist on a per selector basis. The Selector used for receiving connections is never used for creating outbound connections. So, the scenario you outline wouldn&apos;t actually happen. Separating the metrics has compatibility implications and I&apos;m not sure it&apos;s worth it in this case.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16523985" author="enether" created="Tue, 26 Jun 2018 17:06:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m not sure I understand what the appropriate approach would be in that case. You&apos;re saying that a `Selector` would never be used to receive and create connections at once? In that case, this means that `Selector`s which are used for receiving connections show empty connections metrics. Is that so? &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16524060" author="ijuma" created="Tue, 26 Jun 2018 17:55:53 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yes.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16526298" author="rsivaram" created="Thu, 28 Jun 2018 13:20:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;PR: &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/kafka/pull/5301&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/kafka/pull/5301&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
